rgal", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTrack listing:correction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whoracle"}
{"title_page": "N67 road (Ireland)", "text_new": "{{infobox road\n|country=IRL\n|type = N\n|route = 67\n|length_km = 143 \n|destinations = \n* '''[[County Galway]]'''\n*  [[Galway]]\n*  [[Oranmore]]\n*  [[Clarinbridge]]\n*  [[Kilcolgan]]\n*  [[Ballinderreen]]\n*  [[Kinvara]]\n* '''[[County Clare]]'''\n*  [[Ballyvaughan]]\n*  [[Lisdoonvarna]]\n*  [[Kilshanny]]\n*  [[Ennistymon]] \n* [[Lahinch]]\n* [[Miltown Malbay]]\n* [[Quilty]]\n* [[Doonbeg]]\n* [[Kilkee]]\n* [[Kilrush]]\n* [[Killimer]]\n* [[Shannon Ferry]]\n* '''[[County Kerry]]'''\n* [[Tarbert, County Kerry|Tarbert]] \n}}\n\nThe '''N67 road''' is a [[national secondary road]] in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. It runs from [[Galway]] to [[Tarbert, County Kerry|Tarbert]] and passes through [[Oranmore]], [[Clarinbridge]], [[Kinvara]], [[Ballyvaughan]], [[Lisdoonvarna]], [[Ennistymon]], [[Lahinch]], [[Milltown Malbay]], [[Quilty]], [[Doonbeg]] and [[Kilkee]].\n[[File:Sinal de tr\u00e1nsito biling\u00fce preto de Ennistymon.jpg|thumb|220px|left|N67 road sign.]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Roads in Ireland]] \n*[[Motorways in Ireland]]\n*[[National primary road]]\n*[[Regional road (Ireland)|Regional road]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2018/si/434/made/en/print?q=roads Roads Act 1993 (Classification of National Roads) (Amendment) Order 2018] \u2013 [[Department of Transport, Tourism and Sport|Department of Transport]]\n\n{{Roads in Ireland}}\n\n[[Category:National secondary roads in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Roads in County Kerry]]\n[[Category:Roads in County Limerick]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox road\n|country=IRL\n|type = N\n|route = 67\n|length_km = 143 \n|destinations = \n* '''[[County Galway]]'''\n*  [[Galway]]\n*  [[Oranmore]]\n*  [[Clarinbridge]]\n*  [[Kilcolgan]]\n*  [[Ballinderreen]]\n*  [[Kinvara]]\n* '''[[County Clare]]'''\n*  [[Ballyvaughan]]\n*  [[Lisdoonvarna]]\n*  [[Kilshanny]]\n*  [[Ennistymon]] \n* [[Lahinch]]\n* [[Miltown Malbay]]\n* [[Quilty]]\n* [[Doonbeg]]\n* [[Kilkee]]\n* [[Kilrush]]\n* [[Killimer]]\n* [[Shannon Ferry]]\n* '''[[County Kerry]]'''\n* [[Tarbert, County Kerry|Tarbert]] \n}}\n\nThe '''N67 road''' is a [[national secondary road]] in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. It runs from [[Galway]] to [[Tarbert, County Kerry|Tarbert]] and passes though [[Oranmore]], [[Clarinbridge]], [[Kinvara]], [[Ballyvaughan]], [[Lisdoonvarna]], [[Ennistymon]], [[Lahinch]], [[Milltown Malbay]], [[Quilty]], [[Doonbeg]] and [[Kilkee]].\n[[File:Sinal de tr\u00e1nsito biling\u00fce preto de Ennistymon.jpg|thumb|220px|left|N67 road sign.]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Roads in Ireland]] \n*[[Motorways in Ireland]]\n*[[National primary road]]\n*[[Regional road (Ireland)|Regional road]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2018/si/434/made/en/print?q=roads Roads Act 1993 (Classification of National Roads) (Amendment) Order 2018] \u2013 [[Department of Transport, Tourism and Sport|Department of Transport]]\n\n{{Roads in Ireland}}\n\n[[Category:National secondary roads in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Roads in County Kerry]]\n[[Category:Roads in County Limerick]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N67_road_(Ireland)"}
